This paper involves the use of neural networks for policy learning and planning in pixel domains, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of pixel domains also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a possible category. The planning aspect of the algorithm suggests robotics (cs.RO) as another possible category. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning and game theory concepts suggests game theory (cs.GT) as a possible category.
